Hani who was the general secretary of the South African Communist Party was slain on the 10th April 1993 outside his home in Dawn Park Boksburg on the East Rand.The wreath-laying ceremony will be held at Thomas Nkobi Memorial Park in Boksburg. It will be followed in the evening by a memorial lecture at the Boksburg Civic Centre which will be delivered by newly-appointed finance minister Malusi Gigaba.The city said it would also roll out a number of other programmes in Hani s memory.